Global setup:
 Download and install Git
  git config --global user.name "Remo Sanges"
  git config --global user.email noncoding@gmail.com
        
After the creation of a repository from the website:
  mkdir [repo name]
  cd [repo name]
  git init
  touch README
  git add README
  git commit -m 'first commit'
  git remote add origin git@github.com:silverkey/[repo name].git
  git push -u origin master
      
Existing Git Repo:
  cd existing_git_repo
  git remote add origin git@github.com:silverkey/[repo name].git
  git push -u origin master
      
To clone a public repository in a new machine:
  git clone git://github.com/silverkey/[repo name].git
